  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "description",
      "abstract": "Authorizes limited casino gaming in the State at a single casino facility located in the Stadium Development District.  Establishes the Hawaii Gaming Control Commission.  Authorizes the Commission to adopt rules.  Authorizes the Commission to issue one 20-year casino license to one licensee for the development and operation of the casino facility.  Establishes application procedures and requirements for the casino license, supplier's license, and occupational license.  Allows the Commission to establish procedures for the issuance of a liquor license for the casino licensee.  Requires annual reports to the Governor and Legislature.  Establishes the Wagering Tax and the disposition of revenues therefrom, including allocations to the Office of Hawaiian Affairs and Department of Education.  Establishes the State Gaming Fund.  Requires the Commission to establish a Compulsive Gamblers Program.  Requires the Auditor to perform periodic audits of the Commission.  Appropriates funds."
    }
  ],
